      <bioghist>
         
         <head>Biographical Note</head>
         
         <p>Gay rights activist and the first openly gay
		  candidate for public office in North Carolina, resident of
		  Chapel Hill (Orange Co.), N.C.</p>
      
      </bioghist><!--End of biohistory--><!--Begin scopecontent-->
      
      <scopecontent>
         
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         
         <p>Collection contains materials primarily related to
		  the 1984 elections. They include correspondence with public
		  officials (among others), articles, and studies. The
		  materials reflect Brown's interest and involvement in the
		  Democratic Party, national legislation, and issues
		  regarding gay rights.</p>
      
      </scopecontent><!--End scopecontent--><!--Begin controlaccess-->
      
